[1] Cholera - Congo DR (South Kivu)
Date: Tue 7 Sep 2021
Source: Radio Okapi [in French, machine trans., edited]
https://bit.ly/3tuKgbD


The administrator of the territory of Mwenga, Bundya Kika, announced a new epidemic of cholera in this politico-administrative entity of South Kivu. In an interview with Radio Okapi on Tue, 7 Sep 2021, he said he noted 90 new cases in one week with 8 cases of death recorded, specifically in the Kitutu health zone, in the Wamuzimu chiefdom, in the south of Mwenga territory.

"In the Kitutu health zone, there is a cholera disease epidemic. We have already made an official statement. In the past month, there was suspicion of this disease, since many people had diarrhea and vomiting. We took samples. They were sent to the lab from Bukavu for analysis. And this is what confirmed that really it is not diarrhea disease but is cholera," confirmed the administrator of the territory. He explained that the lack of drinking water and the pollution of a local river are among the causes of the resurgence of cholera in Kitutu.

"What we have noticed is linked to the shortage of drinking water and also the water polluted by certain companies which exploited gold, on the Elila river. A large part of the population of Kitutu consumed this as drinking water," Bundya Kika said.

He said he has already taken steps to combat this epidemic: "We have had a lot of meetings with a lot of layers to educate them on how they should behave in this period when the epidemic is raging in Kitutu. And they must respect the hygienic measures which are decreed by the health technicians," indicated Bundya Kika.

--
Communicated by:
Mahmoud Orabi
