[4] Cholera - India (Punjab)
Date: Tue 7 Sep 2021 2:35 PM IST
Source: Tribune News Service [edited]
https://www.tribuneindia.com/news/ludhiana/cholera-case-surfaces-in-ludhiana-307656


One patient suffering from cholera has been detected in the district of Ludhiana. The patient belongs to Valmiki Nagar in Mullanpur and is an 8-year-old child. The patient was admitted to Raghunath Hospital. Cholera has been confirmed in the hanging drop test. The Health Department has swung into action after the confirmation of the case and started a survey in the area. People living in the area of the patient are being tested and awareness is being created.

According to the Health Department, no other person in the area has been found with symptoms of cholera. Chlorine tablets have been distributed in the area and 4 water samples were collected.

